    <div class="container">
        <div class="info">
            <p>A <strong>while loop</strong> in Java is a way to repeat a block of code as long as a specified condition is true. It's like saying, "I want to keep doing this action until something changes." For example, if you want to count from 0 to 4, you can use a while loop to help you do it efficiently!</p>

            <p>Hereâ€™s how a while loop works:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>You start with a condition that checks if you should keep running the loop.</li>
                <li>If the condition is true, the code inside the loop will execute.</li>
                <li>After executing the code, it will check the condition again. If it's still true, the loop will run again.</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Example of a While Loop that Ends:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>int count = 0;
while (count &lt; 5) {
    System.out.println("Count is: " + count);
    count++; // Increment count by 1
}</code></pre>
            <p><strong>Explanation</strong>: In this example, the loop continues as long as <code>count</code> is less than 5. The <code>count</code> variable is incremented in each iteration, which eventually makes the condition false and exits the loop.</p>

            <p><strong>Example of a While Loop that Runs Forever:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>while (true) {
    System.out.println("This loop will run forever!");
}</code></pre>
            <p><strong>Explanation</strong>: In this case, the condition <code>true</code> will always evaluate to true, causing the loop to run indefinitely. This loop will only stop if you interrupt it manually (for example, using Ctrl+C in a terminal or stopping the program in an IDE).</p>

            <p><strong>Important Note</strong>: Be cautious with infinite loops, as they can lead to unresponsive programs if not handled properly! Always ensure you have a way to exit the loop if necessary.</p>
        </div>
        <button class="next-button" onclick="window.location.href='Q1.html'; saveCounter();">Next</button>
